Set Python environment with pyenv
https://github.com/yyuu/pyenv
https://godjango.com/96-django-and-python-3-how-to-setup-pyenv-for-multiple-pythons/


# Get Code
git clone https://github.com/yyuu/pyenv.git ~/.pyenv

# Set the Paths
echo 'export PYENV_ROOT="$HOME/.pyenv"' >> ~/.bashrc
echo 'export PATH="$PYENV_ROOT/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.bashrc

# Initialize pyenv on load of terminal
echo 'eval "$(pyenv init -)"' >> ~/.bashrc

# Restart Shell

# install python
pyenv install 3.5.1

# set python version for current and all sub directories
pyenv local 3.5.1

If some errors appear try the install the following libs:
- build-essential libssl-devel zlib1g-devel libbz2-devel libreadline-devel libsqlite3-devel wget curl llvm libncurses5-devel libncursesw5-devel
Then uninstall python using pyenv and install it again.

pip install -r requirements.txt

